    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "An interesting fight is expected\nwhen the city council meets to.\nnight and the question of paying\nsomething over $4,000 to the Wash.\nington Water Power company\ncomes up.\n\n\nThe company claims that the bill\nis for the city's share Of the paw.\ning Of the collapsed Howard street\nbridge.\n\n\nThe reconstruction OF the col\nlapsed bridge will cost $1,000, OF\nwhich the w. w. p. Co., and the\ncity share alike. If the city recog\nnizes the old bill, 1t will clear the\ncompany of any expense for recon.\nstruction and about $1,000 to boot"
    }
